<br>
Windows barely lit the room - struggling to cast their bright light across the immense span. Yellows, greens and reds from the stained glass pictures of their faces - Faces of all the races and stories of Norrath, Luclin and the Planes. And even a few blank - stark clear - waiting for the next conference - perhaps the one that had been unfolding this day . . .<br>
<br>
A tall man stood, his brow furrowed in worry and exhaustion. His face showing dislike, concealed but poorly for the Teir'dal sitting across the table from him,<br>
<br>
The man speaks, &quot; I do not like what I hear. The winds say if we do not do something then Chaos will prevail and perhaps all will come undone. This cannot happen - Even you can see that. Even you cannot desire that!&quot;<br>
<br>
The Teir'dal nodded. &quot; Yes. It is not good. Total Chaos will not serve us at all. It will bring destruction down upon my people and we will die. I agree with you - balance must be kept. Innoruuk may desire Chaos - but even He sees that total Chaos on our world will not serve. I fear that the disharmony of the races is getting worse! We must do something NOW!! It is the plot of Mischief. Perhaps something to bring all peoples together?&quot; The Teir'dal hesitates and swallows, &quot;A celebration of peace?&quot;<br>
<br>
The man stops almost in shock. He pivots from his pacing in front of a huge fireplace that heats the room's north table edge, &quot; A celebration of peace? YES! In a place of neutrality! Erud's Crossing! A Carnival! A Carnival with prizes and competition and songs and YES that will do it!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
Both stand and stare at each other surprised that they have reached agreement after so many hours of arguing. A carnival at Erud's Crossing. Pausing and looking somewhat doleful they walk toward each other knowing that to keep Chaos from erupting amongst the races of Norrath and slaughter and genocide from occurring between Good and Evil a Carnival might be the answer, they shake hands and part ways - to go make the arrangements.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
